The '''drop table for [[Deadman: Reborn]]''' is accessed by nearly all monsters killed during the game mode, except for [[raids]] and [[Nightmare Zone]].

==Rate of access==
The rate of accessing this table depends on the combat level of the monster. The [[Update:Deadman: Reborn|newspost]] claims that boss monsters have an even higher-than-expected chance of rolling the table, but this could not be confirmed.

The probability of rolling for this table after killing a monster with combat level <math>L</math> is approximately:

For monsters level 1 to 50:
:<math>\mathbb{P} \approx \frac{1}{250 + \left\lfloor (50 - L)^2/5 \right\rfloor}</math>
For monsters level 50 to 150:
:<math>\mathbb{P} \approx \frac{1}{\left\lfloor 337.5 - L/1.75 \right\rfloor}</math>.
For monsters over level 150:
:<math>\mathbb{P} \approx \frac{1}{75}</math>

[[File:Deadman Reborn drop table denominator.png]]

[[Superior slayer monster]]s have a guaranteed chance of rolling on this table.

==Ancient warrior weapons==
''There is approximately a 1/100 chance to roll the Ancient warrior weapons table. Each weapon has an equal chance to be rolled for.''

Monsters in the [[Wilderness]] have a significantly higher chance of rolling for Ancient warrior weapons, believed to be approximately twice as high.
